eval function evaluates the “String”

1.
input = input("Enter any number of your choice:")
print(input)
print(type(input))
--------------------------------------------------------------------Enter any number of your choice: 10 + 10 
10 + 10 
<class 'str'>







2.
eval = eval(input("Enter any number of your choice"))
print(eval)
print(type(eval))
--------------------------------------------------------------------Enter any number of your choice: 10 + 10 
20 
<class 'int'>









3.
evaluate = input(“Enter what operation x has to perform: “)
print(evaluate)
print(type(evaluate))
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Enter what operation x has to perform: x + x + 100 - 35 + 5 * 80 
x + x + 100 - 35 + 5 * 80 
<class 'str'>

x = 10
print(type(x))
--------------------------------------------------------------------
<class 'int'>

expression = eval(evaluate)
print(expression)
print(type(expression))
--------------------------------------------------------------------
485 
<class 'int'>









4. (x,y) = eval(input("Enter two numbers and they will mapped to x and y via eval"))




5 x = eval(input("Enter number that will be string but converted  in int and stored in x via eval"))
